      "summary": "Czechia sat at 32.4% possession in a disciplined 3-5-2, content to absorb South Africa's 584-pass dominance and strike on the counter. SADILEK's 5th-minute goal rewarded the plan perfectly — a clean left-foot finish from a pass — and CZE then defended via 343 total pressures and a deep low block. The 83rd-minute penalty conceded denied a deserved Czech win.",
