    "RSA": {
      "summary": "South Africa dominated possession (60.3%), generated 17 shots, and outplayed Czechia in almost every territorial metric — yet trailed until MOKOENA's 83rd-minute penalty rescued a point. Nasreddine Nabi's 4-3-3 relied on WILLIAMS as a sweeper-keeper to drive build-up from the back, and MOKOENA and MBOKAZI as the key creative conduits, but the final third conversion was painfully lacking until the closing stages.",
